class Solution {
    public int minimumLength(String s) {
        int left = 0, right = s.length() - 1;
        while (left < right && s.charAt(left) == s.charAt(right)) {
            char c = s.charAt(left);
            while (left <= right && s.charAt(left) == c) left++;
            while (left <= right && s.charAt(right) == c) right--;
        }
        return right - left + 1;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The two-pointer technique is used to efficiently remove matching prefixes and suffixes. The algorithm iterates through the string from both ends, removing characters that match at both ends. The remaining substring length is then returned.
